Yesterday, the reporter learned from the Municipal Education Commission that starting this year, the city will pilot the "modern apprenticeship" talent training mode in 60 secondary vocational schools, and the students who receive the pilot training will also have apprenticeship status, and will be pre-recorded as unit employees by the pilot enterprises after enrollment.
According to the requirements of the Municipal Education Commission, Standardize the enrollment procedures of secondary vocational schools and employment procedures of enterprises, Clarify the dual identities of apprentices in secondary vocational schools and prospective employees of enterprises, According to the principle of two-way choice, apprentices, schools and enterprises sign a tripartite agreement. For apprentices who have reached the age of 16 but have not reached the age of 18, apprentices, guardians, schools and enterprises must sign an agreement to determine the rights and interests of all parties and the specific posts, teaching contents and rights and interests protection of apprentices on-the-job training.
Encourage pilot schools to adopt modern apprenticeship and cooperative enterprises to jointly carry out pre-job training and transfer training for employees.
Pilot schools should reform the talent training mode.
Schools and enterprises jointly design personnel training programs, and jointly formulate professional teaching standards, curriculum standards, post standards, enterprise master standards, quality monitoring standards and corresponding implementation plans.
The pilot takes the training academic system as a pilot cycle, and the internship time of students in enterprises is determined according to the professional personnel training plan, and the internship is generally 6 months.
In enterprise practice, the enterprise team management mode should be implemented. According to the characteristics of different majors, one master can take 2 ~ 5 apprentices to form a study group to ensure that students master the skills required by each rotation training post.
According to the arrangement, from 2016 to August 2019, the city has identified 60 pilot projects of modern apprenticeship in municipal secondary vocational schools in three batches, with the number of each pilot project being about 50, and training about 3,000 students (apprentices) in total.
In accordance with the principle of pilot first and then implementation, and gradually advancing from point to point, we will explore the establishment of a long-term mechanism of joint enrollment, joint training and integrated education between schools and enterprises, effectively improve students' job skills, and improve students' counterpart employment rate and employment quality.
