South African doctor: Although Omicron has strong transmission power, it is mostly mild
Many South African doctors and medical experts believe that the Novel Coronavirus Omicron variant is more mild than the Delta variant, although it spreads faster.
According to the Associated Press, with the spread of Omicron variant in South Africa, a physician organization composed of more than 5,000 doctors in Gauteng province, South Africa reported that the COVID-19 patients they are currently treating have mild symptoms, such as body pain and cough, which are similar to influenza.
Dr. Unben Pillay, director of the group, said he sees dozens of patients every day, but none of them need to be hospitalized yet.
"They were able to control the disease at home and most recovered within 10 to 14 days of quarantine," Pillay said.
He said that includes older patients and those with health problems, people who would otherwise be more likely to fall into severe illness due to coronavirus infection.
In contrast, he said, in the last Delta outbreak, the COVID-19 patients he treated "had difficulty breathing and low blood oxygen levels.
Many people will be hospitalized in a few days. ".
In the two weeks since the Omicron variant strain was first reported in southern Africa, other doctors have shared similar experiences.
Although gathering enough data will take several weeks, doctors' observations and early evidence provide some clues.
According to the South African National Institute of Infectious Diseases, only 30% of COVID-19 patients hospitalized in recent weeks are serious diseases, which is half of the severe proportion of the previous epidemic; The average hospitalization time was shortened from 8 days to 2.8 days. Only 3% of the recent COVID-19 patients died, while 20% of the early outbreaks in South Africa died.
"At the moment, almost all the indications are that this is a milder disease," said Willem Hanekom, director of the African Health Institute, citing data from the National Institute of Infectious Diseases and other reports.
He also said: "It is still early, and we need to get later data.
Normally, hospitalizations and deaths occur late, and we are only two weeks into this wave of outbreaks. "
Meanwhile, scientists around the world are looking at case numbers and hospitalization rates while testing the effectiveness of current vaccines and treatments.
Although Delta remains the leading Novel Coronavirus strain worldwide, Omicron cases are emerging in dozens of countries, with South Africa at the epicenter of the outbreak.
Gauteng province saw a 400% increase in new cases detected in the first week of December, according to health officials, and tests showed the Omicron variant accounted for more than 90% of cases.
Education Review: What Should We Rely on to Save Abducted Children?
If we compare the famous public service slogan "No sale, no killing", then in a good environment where there is no demand for "collecting and abducting", mass prevention and treatment, and anti-abduction by the whole people make trafficking unprofitable, risky and costly, and such crimes will not happen frequently.
Recently, the emergency release platform for missing children information developed by the Anti-Abduction Office of the Criminal Investigation Bureau of the Ministry of Public Security was launched.
This is an Internet information platform created to establish an authoritative channel for publishing information on missing children and find abducted children in time.
Hearing that this App is called "Reunion", I feel warm.
The new technical means are not only named "literature and art", but also full of feelings, and the informationization is used properly, practically and effectively.
The primary goal of law enforcement against abduction is to find abducted children and protect their personal safety and freedom.
The second is the trial and punishment of suspects.
The significance of criminal punishment, from individual punishment, social prevention to legal education, can list many "big words".
However, before the trafficking case is solved, priority should be given to the personal safety of the victims.
Prioritize things. Under the urgent purpose of "seeking rescue", controversial topics such as "whether child trafficking should be subject to death" can be temporarily put aside and discussed carefully; But the rescue of abducted children can't wait.
According to the investigation experience of such cases, traffickers are used to staying away from the crime site as soon as possible after they succeed.
If the kidnapping operation is delayed for one more minute, the child may be one step away from the parents, and the difficulty of case detection will increase by one point.
Under such circumstances, it is indeed a pragmatic action to come up with an effective way such as "reunion" platform, which is directly helpful to solve cases and find children.
After all, "abduction" is a big task that needs to operate the whole legal system.
To crack down on crime and protect the rights and interests of children and parents, from the perfection of legislation to the guarantee of justice and the meticulous law enforcement, it is necessary to implement the care of "protecting the young and helping the weak".
In addition, the prevention of child trafficking, from family to society, can be done better.
For example, in a common case, a family of three rested at the railway station, and their parents slept soundly, only to wake up to find that their children were gone.
A two-year-old child can't be expected to have enough self-protection skills, but as a parent of a young child, he should at least have a considerable sense of protection.
Parents take turns to rest, or put their children under safe protection, which are the minimum means to prevent children from being abducted.
From the other side of the police's crackdown on trafficking crimes, the party who buys abducted children should also be paid attention to and punished.
A single illegal act is often just a link in a long chain.
According to China's Criminal Law, the starting point of legal punishment in crime of trafficking in children is 5 years; If the circumstances are particularly serious, they may be sentenced to death and confiscated of property.
Under the general trend of "light punishment", crime of trafficking in children is obviously a crime with heavier punishment.
But there are still many cases of trafficking every year.
It can be seen that some people have backward concepts and weak legal awareness in raising children.
The legal education for these people should be followed up simultaneously.
To effectively control the crime of trafficking, we can't rely solely on the strict enforcement of the law by the government.
If the "market" of abduction exists widely, the traffickers are greedy for profit, constantly innovate the means of abduction, and form a situation of "fighting against the law" with law enforcers, and the anti-abduction action is bound to fall into an inefficient quagmire.
Therefore, getting rid of backward concepts and popularizing legal knowledge will also help to eradicate the crime of trafficking and buying children.
