Don't scare people at the starting line-Xinhuanet
When visiting the book market, you can often feel the popularity of successful books.
Many of today's success books preach the "best principle"-that is, assuming or implying that you can "do it" before telling you what you need to do.
It is equivalent to saying that "how to do it" is actually the most important and fundamental link.
For this reason, these books all have a common feature-either do the best in one go, or do nothing at all; Either 100 or 0; Either you will climb Mount Tai, or you will simply stay where you are.
This "best principle" will admit that it is "extremely correct", but 99% of people will be intimidated before the starting line.
Because this theory advocates a path of "you have to make up your mind, turn over a new leaf, and make a great change of 180 degrees", which is precisely the fatal weakness of many people.
For those who stick to the rules, follow the old ways and refuse to change, you have to shout "You want to change" in his ear, which is undoubtedly self-deception and casting pearls before swine.
The vast majority of people will make a fool of oneself in front of the word "change", and it is difficult to make up their minds; Or, with a temporary impulse, I made a painful determination to "change" and bravely took the first step, but it often didn't last long, and I couldn't persist for a while before I lost, so it was difficult to see continuity.
Mr. Ma Sanli's famous crosstalk "Starting from Tomorrow" is the classic that vividly shows this "universal humanity".
The biggest problem of the "best principle" is that the threshold is too high, which often exceeds the ability limit of ordinary people and makes most people "look at the door and sigh".
Perhaps, the "second best principle" is a possible way for more ordinary people to embark on the road of relative success.
The core of the "second best principle" lies in "lowering the threshold"-it encourages a theory of "accumulating small wins into big wins", that is, if you can't do 100, you can only do 1: because 1 is always greater than 0; If you can't climb Mount Tai, just climb the small sand dunes in front of your house, because it is better than standing still.
In a word, as long as you do something, it is better than nothing.
Because the threshold is greatly lowered, it is more possible for ordinary people to persist, and as long as they persist in everything, the probability of success will increase.
It's just that the road to success following the "second best principle" is slightly longer.
To sum up, although the "best principle" is ostensibly under the banner of making everyone succeed, what it can inspire in the end is actually a few; The "second best principle" can effectively motivate more people and benefit more people as much as possible.
The reserves of naked carp resources in Qinghai Lake increased by 7,100 tons this year-Xinhuanet
Xinhua News Agency, Xining, December 11 (Reporter Luo Xiaofei, Zhang Hongxiang) The reporter learned from the Agriculture and Rural Department of Qinghai Province that the latest monitoring results showed that the reserves of naked carp resources in Qinghai Lake increased by 7,100 tons this year compared with the previous year, reaching 108,500 tons, which was more than 40 times higher than the initial protection period in 2002.
Naked carp in Qinghai Lake, commonly known as "Huangyu", is a unique and precious fish species in Qinghai Lake, which plays an important role in maintaining the safety and biodiversity of "water-fish-bird" ecological chain in Qinghai Lake Basin.
In 1960s and 1970s, the number of naked carp in Qinghai Lake dropped sharply due to factors such as mass hunting and degradation of the breeding water environment of naked carp. In 2002, the reserves of naked carp resources in Qinghai Lake were only 2,592 tons.
In 2004, Qinghai Lake naked carp was listed as an endangered species in the Red List of Chinese Species.
Since 2003, Qinghai Province has closed the lake to raise fish, prohibiting any unit, collective or individual from fishing naked carp in Qinghai Lake and its main rivers and tributaries, and prohibiting the sale of naked carp and its products.
At the same time, through artificial proliferation and release, cleaning up the main rivers entering Qinghai Lake, designing scientific and reasonable "fish passage" and other measures, the reserves of naked carp resources in Qinghai Lake have increased year by year.
Yang Lin, deputy director of Qinghai Provincial Department of Agriculture and Rural Affairs, said that up to now, nearly 180 million naked carp in Qinghai Lake have been artificially proliferated and released, contributing more than 23% to the recovery of naked carp resources in Qinghai Lake.
The Sanjiangyuan region of Qinghai is an important ecological barrier and water conservation area in China and even in Asia, while Qinghai Lake is a natural barrier and ecological functional area to control the eastward spread of desertification in western China.
In order to protect the ecological environment of Sanjiangyuan region and Qinghai Lake waters, protect aquatic wild animals and maintain the biodiversity of Qinghai-Tibet Plateau, Qinghai has successively issued notices on fishing ban in key waters of Yangtze River, Yellow River and Qinghai Lake since this year, and established a comprehensive fishing ban management system of "one river, one river and one lake".
