Xinhua News Agency, Tianjin, December 12 (Reporter Zhou Runjian) Astronomical science experts said that as the last large-scale meteor shower this year, Geminid meteor shower, one of the three major meteor showers in the Northern Hemisphere, will usher in a great deal on December 14, and friends who like meteor shower can observe it in the middle of the night.
An Jiu, an astronomy enthusiast in Beijing, photographed the Geminid meteor shower in Qinghai on December 13, 2018.
The parent body of most meteor showers is periodic comets, but the parent body of Geminid meteor shower is asteroid Phaeton No.3200, which is an Apollo asteroid.
Geminid meteor shower is also the second known meteor shower that is not "bred" by comets.
Xiu Lipeng, director of Tianjin Astronomical Society and expert in astronomical science popularization, said that just like New Year's blockbusters, Geminid meteor showers generally appear at the end of the year, and the "release schedule" can last from December 4th to 17th.
This meteor shower is famous for its large and stable flow, and is called the three major meteor showers in the Northern Hemisphere together with quadrant meteor shower and Perseid meteor shower.
A notable feature of Geminid meteor shower is that meteoroids are slow, colorful and have many fireball, which is suitable for both visual and astrophotography beginners.
Yang Jing, an astronomy enthusiast in Tianjin, photographed the Geminid meteor shower in Jizhou, Tianjin on December 13, 2020.
Astronomical forecast shows that this year's Geminid meteor shower will usher in a maximum at around 15:00 on December 14th, and the ZHR (the number of meteors that can be seen per hour when the radiation point is directly above the head under ideal observation conditions) is 150.
Recommended index map of Geminid meteor shower.
"Last year, people were deeply impressed by the colorful Geminid meteor shower, but this year's Geminid meteor shower will be disturbed by moonlight, and the wonderful degree will be discounted a little.
14th is November 11th of the lunar calendar, and the moon phase is full and convex. Bright moonlight will interfere with observation. Fortunately, the moon will set in the middle of the night, and the radiation point of Geminid meteor shower will rise higher at this time.
Friends who like meteor showers can observe in the last few hours when the moon falls behind in the middle of the night, but pay attention to cold and warmth. "
How can we observe as many meteors as possible?
"It is not recommended to observe in cities. You can choose a place with high altitude, little light damage and wide field of vision facing northeast in suburbs or villages, and then wait patiently until the moon sets for visual observation.
It should be noted that the flow of Geminid meteor shower in all directions is very large, so it is not necessary to stare at the radiation point of Geminid meteor shower all the time during observation.
Friends who like photography want to shoot gorgeous meteor shower movies, it is best to choose a wide-angle and large aperture lens, and use high ISO and maximum aperture when shooting.
Based on stability and continuity, tripods, backup batteries and cable release are also essential. "
Xiu Lipeng reminded.
